"Tosi L., Carbognin L., Teatini P., Strozzi T., Wegmüller U.","Evidence of the present relative land stability of Venice, Italy, from land, sea, and space observations",2002,"Geophysical Research Letters","29","12",,"3","1 - 3-4",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0037098775&partnerID=40&md5=63f4226227544e346055e51de77a4922","Istituto per lo Studio Della Dinamica Delle Grandi Masse, National Research Council, Venezia, Italy; Department of Mathematical Methods and Models for Scientific Applications, University of Padova, Padova, Italy; Gamma Remote Sensing, Muri BE, Switzerland","Tosi, L., Istituto per lo Studio Della Dinamica Delle Grandi Masse, National Research Council, Venezia, Italy; Carbognin, L., Istituto per lo Studio Della Dinamica Delle Grandi Masse, National Research Council, Venezia, Italy; Teatini, P., Department of Mathematical Methods and Models for Scientific Applications, University of Padova, Padova, Italy; Strozzi, T., Gamma Remote Sensing, Muri BE, Switzerland; Wegmüller, U., Gamma Remote Sensing, Muri BE, Switzerland","The city of Venice is very vulnerable to loss in surface elevation as a result of subsidence and eustacy because of its small elevation above sea level. The alarm of the scientific community related to this persistent problem is increasing because of the forecasts of sea level rise caused by global warming. In order to evaluate the present relative subsidence of Venice, a study has been performed by combining high precision leveling, Satellite Radar Interferometry (SRI) and tide gauge measurements. The analysis of the most recent data points out with an unprecedented detail the present ground stability of the city.",,"Interferometry; Radar; Satellites; Sea level; Tide gages; Land stability; Geophysics; eustacy; global warming; leveling; radar interferometry; sea level change; subsidence; tide gauge; Italy",,,,,,"Amelung, F., Galloway, D.L., Bell, J.W., Zebker, H.H., Laczniak, R.J., Sensing the ups and downs of Las Vegas: InSAR reveals structural control (1999) Geology, 27, pp. 483-486; Bamler, R., Hartl, P., Synthetic aperture radar interferometry (1998) Inverse Problems, 14, pp. R1-R54; Bergamasco, A., Teatini, P., Carbognin, L., Confronto critico tra kriging e analisi oggettiva (1993) II Nuovo Cimento, 16 C (3), pp. 289-302; Bonardi, M., Canal, E., Cavazzoni, S., Serandrei, R., Tosi, L., Impact of paleoclimatic fluctuations on depositional environments and (1998) World Resource Review, 11, pp. 247-257; Carbognin, L., Taroni, G., Eustatismo a Venezia e Trieste nell'ultimo secolo (1996) Atti Istituto Veneto di Scienze, Lettere ed Arti, 154, pp. 281-298; Carbognin, L., Tosi, L., Teatini, P., Analysis of actual land subsidence in Venice, Italy (1995) Land Subsidence, pp. 129-137. , edited by F. B. J. Barends, F. J. J. Brower, and F. H. Schröder, A; Carbognin, L., Gatto, P., Marabini, F., (1984) The City and the Lagoon of Venice: A Guidebook on the Environment and, , publication issued on occasion of the 3rd Int. Symp. on Land Subsidence; Carbognin, L., Gatto, P., Mozzi, G., Gambolati, G., Ricceri, G., New trend in the subsidence of Venice (1977) Land Subsidence, 121, pp. 65-81. , edited by J. C. Rodda IAHS Publ; Gambolati, G., Gatto, P., Freeze, R.A., Mathematical simulation of the subsidence of Venice. 2, results (1974) Water Resour. Res, 10 (3), pp. 563-577; Gatto, P., Carbognin, L., The lagoon of Venice: Natural environmental trend and man-induced (1981) Hydrol. Sci. Bull, 26 (4), pp. 379-391; Strozzi, T., Wegmüller, U., Tosi, L., Bitelli, G., Spreckels, V., Land subsidence monitoring with differential SAR interferometry (2001) Photogram. Eng. and Remote Sensing, 67 (11), pp. 1261-1270; Tosi, L., Carbognin, L., Teatini, P., Rosselli, R., Gasparetto Stori, G., The ISES project subsidence monitoring of the catchment basin south of (2000) Land Subsidence, 2, pp. 113-126. , edited by L. Carbognin, G. Gambolati, and A. I. Johnson, La Garangola; Tsimplis, M.N., Baker, T.F., Sea